137  void parseFormula(
138  const Mutation::Thermodynamics::Thermodynamics& thermo,
139  const SurfaceState& surf_state,
140  const Mutation::Utilities::IO::XmlElement& node_reaction)
141  {
142  std::string reactants;
143  std::string products;
144  splitFormulainReactantsProducts(reactants, products, node_reaction);
145 
146  parseSpecies(m_reactants, m_reactants_surf,
147  reactants, node_reaction, thermo, surf_state);
148  parseSpecies(m_products, m_products_surf,
149  products, node_reaction, thermo, surf_state);
150  }
151 
152 //==============================================================================
157  virtual void splitFormulainReactantsProducts(
158  std::string& reactants, std::string& products,
159  const Mutation::Utilities::IO::XmlElement& node_reaction)
160  {
161  size_t pos_equal = m_formula.find("=");
162  if(pos_equal == std::string::npos){
163  node_reaction.parseError(
164  (std::string("Reaction formula ") + m_formula
165  + std::string(" does not have '=' or '=>'!")).c_str());
166  }
167 
168  reactants = m_formula.substr(0, pos_equal);
169  products = m_formula.substr(pos_equal + 2, m_formula.length()
170  - pos_equal - 1);
171  }
